original_title: Palestine Ambassador meets State Minister of Tourism
original_body_lines: A special meeting by Ambassador of Palestine to Sri Lanka Dr. Zuhair M.H. Zaid this week with State Minister of Tourism Diana Gamage highlighted the long history of cooperation between Palestine and Sri Lanka as well as the support they have extended to development of the tourism sector in Sri Lanka. Private Secretary to the State Minister of Tourism Dr. Arosha Fernando, Parliament Secretary of the State Minister of Tourism Lahiru Anushka, and Media Secretary of the State Tourism Ministry Niranjan De Alwis too attended the discussion.
